#Anything you write onto the .env file is not uploaded or made visible when the project is uploaded onto Github.
# Whenever we make a project on Supabase, it stores our database onto one of Supabase Servers. When we try to integrate the database into our project, frontend needs to know which database to connect to and prove that it has permission to interact with that project.
# Project URL tells the specific project on the Supabase Servers that frontend needs to connect to.
# Anon Key is the public API key. It tells Supabase that the request is coming from a user/project/application that is allowed to use the public features of this project.